tiative and punish you for your brave opening choice.Thus, working on this chapter lead to some sort of conundrum - on one hand you are constantly looking at computer evaluations that are very much in White's favour, but on the other hand, I knew that the majority of these evaluations are not 100% relevant for practical play ( Something similar happened as I was working on my course on the Modern defence, although you could make an argument that the Four Pawns Attack is a more narrow battlefield than 1.e4 g6 ). I tried to take this into account when choosing my recommendation in this chapter and I have tried to find a good balance between what is objectively the best - and what I think can pose significant practical problems!} 
