12. Bf1 {This move looks quite natural, as it is quite logical to open up the e-file for the rook.} 
12. e5 {Now with the inclusion of the moves 11...Rc8 12. Bf1 we do indeed strike in the center.} 
13. Bg5 {The only real try for an advantage, trying to disrupt Black's harmony and obtain a good version of the queenless middlegame.} 
13. Qd7
14. dxe5 {Note that14.g4doesn't quite work due to14...Nxd415.gxf5Qxf5when Black regains a piece with a won position.} 
