8. a4 {This will be White's reaction in 99% of the cases. Once again, we will see in the mainline with the queen on h5 how to deal with alternative moves such as8.a3or8.c3and the same methods can be applied here.} 
8. Nc6 {Hitting the exposed pawn on e5 with a gain of tempo (Highlighting, therefore, the drawback of not having the queen on h5) and also preparing to jump Nd4.} 
9. Qg3
9. Nd4 {A very good move, intending to eliminate the bishop on b3 and grab the bishop pair.} 
10. Nc3
