12. cxb3
12. Bc6
13. O-O
13. Qd3 {And now the queen will move to g6, after which we will be ready to develop the bishop on f8 and castle our king. White knights have some good outposts such as the one on b5, but we do have a bishop pair and a very healthy structure. Even though a lot of chess remains to be played, we can be more than happy with the outcome of the opening.} 
