5. Bb3 {Of course, the bishop wasn't developed to c4 to immediately depart from the a2-g8 diagonal, so this is the only move really worth analyzing.} 
5. dxe5 {As mentioned above and as we have seen over and over agian in this chapter - since White refrained from reinforcing the e5 pawn on the previous move, we are more than happy to capture it, open the d-file and create a potential target on e5.} 
6. Qh5 {The main move in this position, eyeing the f7 pawn and also adding some control to the e5 square.} 
